===Etymology===
Probably cognate with {{och-l|景|bright}}, {{och-l|影|shadow}} ({{zh-ref|Wang, 1982}}; {{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}; {{zh-ref|Baxter and Sagart, 2014}}). {{zh-ref|Gong (2019)}} identifies the unknown preinitial ''*C'' in the reconstruction {{IPAfont|*C.qraŋʔ-s}} by {{zh-ref|Baxter and Sagart (2014)}} with ''*s'' based on evidence from Old Vietnamese, and further posits that it is an instrumental noun derived by prefixation of ''*s-'' to the verb {{och-l|映|id=2|to reflect}}, which is itself a denominal derived from {{och-l|影|shadow; image}}; however, Gong acknowledges that his emendation of {{IPAfont|*C.qraŋʔ-s}} to {{IPAfont|*s.qraŋʔ-s}} is incompatible with {{w|Reconstructions of Old Chinese#Baxter–Sagart (2014)|Baxter & Sagart's 2014 system}}, as {{IPAfont|*s.qraŋʔ-s}} would have become Middle Chinese {{IPAfont|*tsrjaeŋH}} instead of {{IPAfont|*kjaeŋH}} ([[ibid.]]).

Alternatively, it may be derived from {{och-l|亮|to shine}} with the nominalising *''k-'' prefix ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}; ''[[apud]]'' Baxter, [[p.c.]]).

STEDT compares {{lang|zh|鏡}}, {{lang|zh|景}} and {{lang|zh|亮}}, among others, to {{cog|tbq-kuk-pro|*klaaŋ-I}}, {{m|tbq-kuk-pro|*klaan-II||to shine; light; bright}}.

This word is relatively late and is perhaps re-etymologized from the nearly identical earlier word {{och-l|監|id=2}}, {{och-l|鑑|id=2|mirror}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}), which {{zh-ref|Wang (1982)}} treats as cognate. {{zh-ref|Gong (2019)}} considers {{lang|zh|鏡}} to be an unrelated neologism replacing {{lang|zh|鑑}}.

